Note that this method introduces a natural classiï¬cation

of multipartite states. We have to add a unitary Uk as a variable only if i1ÃÃÃil;k Â¼ i1ÃÃÃil  1k for some properly chosen i1 Ã Ã Ã il. The worst case, i.e., the case which in-
volves the largest number of variables, occurs for maxi-

mally entangled states (all bipartite splittings are

maximally entangled). In this case, which exists only for

certain instances of n, we have dn=2e unitaries as variables.

